Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounces}(halved lengthwise). Halve, peel, and cut
@red onion{1}(peeled and cut into ½-inch-thick wedges). Trim, peel, and cut
@carrots{6%ounces}(peeled and cut on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces).
Quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss Brussels sprouts, onion, and carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle
of @olive oil{2%teaspoons}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-22%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounces} dry with #paper towels{} and season
all over with @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @dried thyme{¼%tsp}, salt, and pepper.
(You'll use more thyme later.)

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes} per side.

> If chicken is on the thicker side, reduce heat to low; cook 2-3 minutes more
> per side.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wash out pan;
let cool ~{1%minute}.

Return pan to medium-high heat; add @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @cranberry jam{1},
¼ cup @water{}, ¼ tsp thyme, and @sugar{¼%tsp}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
sauce has thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and juice from one lemon wedge (juice from two wedges
for 4). Season with salt and pepper to taste.

> Add another squeeze of lemon juice if desired.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken and veggies between plates. Drizzle chicken with as much pan sauce
as you like. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.